org.gearvrf.physics

Class GVRRigidBody

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.gearvrf.GVRHybridObject
      • org.gearvrf.GVRComponent
        • org.gearvrf.physics.GVRRigidBody

  • public class GVRRigidBody
extends org.gearvrf.GVRComponent
    Represents a rigid body that can be static or dynamic. You can set a mass and apply some physics forces.

    By default it is a static body with infinity mass, value 0, and does not move under simulation. A dynamic body with a mass defined is fully simulated.

    Every scene object can represent a rigid body since it has a GVRRigidBody component attached to. You must setup the values of owner's GVRTransform, like initial position, and the mass value of the rigid body before attach it to its owner.
